<br><Br>
<img src = http://www.rit.edu/~jgs1536/media/makino.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umertondraco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merton Draco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Devout Worshipper of<br>Rangers and Paladins...</span><br>  Posts: 780<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/7/01 9:46:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nerf City</span><hr size=1> Paladins suck.  Deal with it.  They will always suck.  Deal with it.<br>
<br>
<br>
It wouldn't make any sense to go down the list of all dragons and start tagging them immune to silence or non-immune because chances are all the dragons who would be tagged as not immune to silence, are trivial encounters anyways.  You either make a spell that has a chance(no matter how small) to stick on all the mobs or you dont make it all.<br>
<br>
Now if you want a solution...  how about this:  Have the Silence spell have a 20 second duration and about 20 minute recast time, or something similar.  It will block a few AE's but it can be used only 1-2 times per fight.  <br>
<br>
<br>
And one last thing, having a spell like this is an insult to guilds who worked their asses off and had to deal with mobs like Aaryonar, taking the full brunt of AE's, only to have some n00b guild waltz in 4 months later into ToV-N with an assload of paladins and happily skip their way to phat lewtz.  The accomplishments themselves are trivialized. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umertondraco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merton Draco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Devout Worshipper of<br>Rangers and Paladins...</span><br>  Posts: 781<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/7/01 9:56:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nerf City</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
And the problem with this is.... what?<br>
<br>
Before you smack me around... why didn't they just make the mobs who use AE as primary damage like this immune to silence? I mean, there are mobs that are immune to slow... why not silence?<br>
<br>
I'd rather have some uber mobs not be able to be silenced than to not have silence itself. /sigh<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Are you still lvl 40 something?  Just curious.<br>
<br>
Its a lot easier to decide which mobs can be slowed than which mobs can AE because... (and I'm sure this will be a huge shock to you) ...dragons do most of their damage and raid disruption(fears/silence/slow) through... AE.<br>
<br>
If you can land a slow on the dragon, that helps a good deal but doesn't trivialize the encounter, just makes tha clerics job easier to keep the MT alive.  If you block the AE, then all you have is the mob's l33t melee skillz while your friendly neighborhood zerg force r0x0rz him with 60 people.<br>
<br>
